Package keystone.api.wrappers.blocks

Class BlockMask

java.lang.Object
keystone.api.wrappers.blocks.BlockMask
public class BlockMask extends Object
A block mask for a filter. Used to restrict operations to either only a set of blocks or every block except a set of blocks

      public static void buildForcedAdditionsList()

      INTERNAL USE ONLY, DO NOT USE IN FILTERS

      Create the forced block additions list. Currently, this is used to bind all variants of air together.

    • withAllVariants

      public BlockMask withAllVariants(String block)
      Add a property agnostic block ID to the mask. Any valid block ID or block tag ID will work. Blocks added in this way will match any variant of the block. For example, adding "minecraft:stone_slab" will match "minecraft:stone_slab[type=top]" and "minecraft:stone_slab[type=bottom]"
      Parameters:
      block - The block ID to add
      Returns:
      The modified BlockMask

    • withAllVariants

      public BlockMask withAllVariants(BlockType blockType)

      Parameters:
      blockType - The BlockType to add
      Returns:
      The modified BlockMask

    • isBlacklist

      public boolean isBlacklist()

      Whether this BlockMask is a blacklist. If true, this will match all blocks except the mask contents
